snippet.textDisplay: You know it’s sad to see that even though Justin is completely being himself and being open about his life and what he has gone through, our world still judges. No one is perfect, and he does say that. We all understand the fact that not everyone will agree on certain things or like each other. So, why still judge and be hurtful to one another? Everyone is trying to find their purpose in life and that is one thing we can agree on. Justin and Hailey are human beings, just like us. They are going to have their ups and downs, just like us. I would like to believe they are in love, and even if they aren’t or one of them was using the other for one reason or another, it’s no one’s business. We would like to think it is because they’re “celebrities,” but it really isn’t. I’m in no way trying to offend anyone, I just simply want our world to understand each other. Wouldn’t you want to be understood rather than being judged?

I’ve been through what he is going through and still am ... it’s anxiety. I suffered from mini attacks all my life.. I suspect for him it’s a byproduct from excessive dopamine levels as a child and now his body is not regulating his hormones properly. He is strong... stronger than you can imagine because when you go through this your body is screaming for you to stop and there’s nothing you can do to make it better... you just suffer through the anxiety wave. For me I learned how to control my anxiety through meditation and eating healthy. I pray I’m wrong and this is just withdraw symptoms... at any rate this is a dangerous place to be in and I hate to say it but someone needs to keep an eye on him and watch for suicidal tendencies.

Justin bud if you are reading this your not alone.

snippet.textDisplay: It’s really complicated to understand the anxiety, damage and stress this person went through as a young boy. And it’s not just him, it’s these people surrounded by fame and being constantly seen us lucky people. Something I have learned is that every person gets lost in life, it’s when they fully face the reality of it, everything gets dark because they become disappointed. It’s hard to adapt to something so cruel, since small children we all believe life is a fairytale. But this is twice as complicated with celebrities like him, who have so many judgemental eyes on him.  But then again there is the healing process, which he is going through right now. They have a story that they’ll carry with them their whole life.
